  "description": "Fix Blank Grey Space Below Image Error State\n\nRemove unwanted blank grey space appearing at the bottom of the responsive-image-wrapper component when it's in an error state (image-error class applied).\n\nRequirements:\n- Inspect the CSS for responsive-image-wrapper when image-error class is present\n- Identify the source of the grey space (padding, margin, min-height, aspect-ratio, or placeholder dimensions)\n- Adjust styling to eliminate the blank space while maintaining proper error state display\n- Ensure the fix works across different viewport sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)\n- Verify the error state still displays correctly (error icon, message, or fallback content)\n- Test that successful image loading is not affected by the fix",
